'''Françoise Bertin''' (23 September 1925 – 26 October 2014) was a [[France|French]] [[actress]].

She appeared in over 125 films since 1961. Among these were five films directed by [[Alain Resnais]]: ''[[Last Year at Marienbad]]'', ''[[Muriel (film)|Muriel]]'', ''[[The War Is Over (1966 film)|The War Is Over]]'', ''[[I Want to Go Home (1989 film)|I Want to Go Home]]'', and ''[[Same Old Song]]''.

Born in [[Paris]] on 23 September 1925, she died in [[Galan, Hautes-Pyrénées]], on 26 October 2014.<ref>{{cite news|title=Décès de la comédienne Françoise Bertin|trans-title=Death of actress Françoise Bertin|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/culture/article/2014/10/27/deces-de-la-comedienne-francoise-bertin_4513273_3246.html|agency=[[Agence France-Presse|AFP]]|work=[[Le Monde]]|date=27 October 2014|accessdate=13 May 2019|language=fr}}</ref>

